redux-saga is used to write
and fetch data asynchronously
from the network or indexedDB.
This is where RPC calls are
made to fetch blocks,
transactions, events,
and manage subscriptions.
Sagas then dispatch new
actions to update the state.

div.div:
Redux state is an in-memory
JSON object modified by actions
and reducers.
We need this to store non-encodable
objects that are instantiated using
data from the persistent state.
For example Web3.eth.Contract
objects used for contract calls
and event subscriptions are
instantiated using the stored
address and ABI.

div.div:
IndexedDB is the modern browser
database we use for persistent
storage and indexing.
IndexedDB supports compound
indices which enable efficient
querying of data.

For example, ContractEvent
can be searched by specific time
ranges and specific addresses.
Pagination is also supported with
limit and offset query parameters.
